hopobject.body: What do you study? toprol mg At the Frankfurt show, BMW reinforced its commitment to the future of electric and hybrid cars. Or more like staking a claim in the present and now, with global launches for the i3 electric – to be available only in select global cities (no plans for Dubai at the moment) – and the i8 hybrid supercar, which can throw up 400-hp and costs a cool 130,000 euros for the pleasure. Expect the i8 to make it here by mid next year. (But high-performance car fanatics can get a look-in at the Dubai Motor Show in November.)
